import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.lineplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=data)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the trend of budget allocation over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    ax = sns.histplot(data=data, x='value', kde=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Value')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of forecast values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['budgetYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['budgetYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['forecastYear'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecastYear'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    chart_data = data.groupby('budgetYear')['value'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='budgetYear', y='value', data=chart_data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average budget allocation per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
